A young scholar Kao Ching (Yeung Yeung) accompanied by his cousin Fu Kun (Steve Chan Ho) travels to Beijing to take an exam. The female ghost possessing Fu Kun is exorcised by a noble priest., Wang Che Cheng (Ngai So).
 As their journey continues, Fu Kun is possessed again by the female Green-Clad ghost (Kiu Lam).
 Along the way, Kao Ching becomes captivated by a Miss Hu Yen (Margaret Hsing Hui) and delays his journey. They enter a house filled with ghosts and after a misunderstanding between the fox-fairies and followers of the Green-Clad ghost, a fight ensures and the fox-fairies are defeated. Still possessed, Fu Kun seeks help from some monks who planned to capture Miss Yu Yen.
 Kao Ching prevents this and in return she promises to help Fu Kun defeat the female ghosts.
